cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.NE

The paper discusses complex-valued convolutional networks and their applications in signal processing, time series modeling, and image analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of wavelets and renormalization group theory, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE), respectively.
